<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-246-216 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 785 323</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDGE on andamp; about ATandamp;T  Jan 7, 1991 v6 n128 p7(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EDGE Publishing 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Western Union: sells $180 million assets to ATandamp;T to pay debts.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (Investment activities)Western Union Corp. (Divestment).andO;Ticker:    T.andO;Topic:     BondsFinancial StabilityBankruptcyCommunications Service SuppliersDivestmentDebt.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Western Union, hoping to avoid involuntary bakruptcy completed a deal onMonday, December 31, to sell $180 million in assets to ATandamp;T to pay off someholders of junk bonds.andM;The company sold its telex and Easy Link electronic mail businesses and wasusing $175 million in net proceeds to pay investors 50 cents on the dollarfor securities with a face value of $335 million.andM;Western Union's debt still stands at $311 million and the company is stillnot out of the woods.andM;Under the December 31 transaction, the company is buying back $329 millionworth of 19 1/4 percent notes and $6 million of 16 percent notes frominvestors who accepted the offer by Thursday, January 3, 1991.andM;The transaction eases the threat of involuntary bankruptcy, which has doggedthe company since it missed a $51 million interest payment in JuneandM;Western Union has told creditors that further refinancing of debt will berequired in 1991 and that that could mean selling more assets, offering newdeals to investors or securing new financing.andM;Western Union filed a statement in late November with the Securities andExchange Commission saying it could fall $70 million short of its obligationsin 1991 and more than $200 million short in 1992.andM;ATandamp;T plans to create a new unit, ATandamp;T Easy Link, headed up by Gordon Bridge.andO;ATandamp;T will combine business communication services it previously offered withthe telex and Easy Link electronic mail services.andO;</TEXT></DOC>